title: PPPP Abdul Aziz wins PS-80 election
content:
ISLAMABAD, Feb 9 (APP): Pakistan People’s Party Parliamentarians’ (PPPP) Abdul Aziz Junejo has won the Sindh Assembly election from PS-80, Dadu-I by securing 52,131 votes.
According to the unofficial result issued by Returning Officer/ECP, his runner-up was Karim Ali Jotoi of, the Grand Democratic Alliance, who bagged votes of 43815.
Overall voters’ turn-out remained 41.9 %.
